The chinks in the armour soon started to show. Trump surrounded himself with close family and sycophants. It was one scandal after another, with several close associates ending up in jail.
The shenanigans were reminiscent of a mafia family. The White House was starting to look and sound like some State House in the third world countries Trump had dismissed in unprintable terms.
Celebrities
But, as many celebrities know only too well, the thrill of adulation carries the self-destruct seed in form of that old trait, hubris, which, became increasingly troubling when Trump rode roughshod over science and held political rallies that exposed thousands to Covid-19.
 Then he started to look like a colonial governor presiding over rival tribes, using divide-and-rule tactics to reward friendly states and threaten to penalise those who didn’t toe the line. He expected judges to overturn election results and hand him the presidency as though they owed allegiance to him.



