America was going to go it alone, dismissing global warming as a hoax, withdrawing from the Paris Accord, the United Nations Human Rights Commission, abandoning the WHO in the middle of the biggest pandemic of our generation.
A complete repudiation of multilateralism and global cooperation. For Trump, even the EU and Nato were objects of disdain. The utterances and actions made the USA something of a loose cannon, which wasn’t helped by the never-ending charade of the president’s twitter feed.
Trump’s base accepted that too many resources and energies had been diverted from home where charity is supposed to begin, by a president they were prepared to believe was foreign-born.
President Obama was perceived as being too keen to engage, to embrace, to sign treaties, to forge partnerships, even to accept the rise of China.
While many Trumpian values will remain, for now, the experiment has come to an end.
